1
00:00:00,166 --> 00:00:02,041
Everyone here was Arab

2
00:00:02,666 --> 00:00:03,708
There were no others among them

3
00:00:03,916 --> 00:00:05,583
Interviewer: By Arabs, you
mean they held Arab nationalities?

4
00:00:05,583 --> 00:00:08,583
Meaning they were
from Iraq, Iraqis

5
00:00:10,041 --> 00:00:14,041
And most of them were
from the outskirts of Mosul

6
00:00:14,166 --> 00:00:16,333
Interviewer: From the villages? Witness:
From the villages and surrounding areas

7
00:00:17,041 --> 00:00:20,291
I personally did not see anyone
among them from Mosul city

8
00:00:21,541 --> 00:00:25,666
Interviewer: You did not
see? Or there were none at all?

9
00:00:25,708 --> 00:00:30,291
There were people from Mosul,
but not from our neighborhoods

10
00:00:30,291 --> 00:00:33,833
Rather from areas like
Rajm Hadid and Hay al-Tank

11
00:00:35,166 --> 00:00:36,708
And areas even farther away

12
00:00:37,291 --> 00:00:42,541
But I did not see anyone from
the original residents of Mosul

13
00:00:43,166 --> 00:00:46,166
As I told you, whoever argued
with them and pushed further

14
00:00:47,708 --> 00:00:49,583
They dealt with him differently

15
00:00:49,666 --> 00:00:50,791
That is why you could not speak

16
00:00:50,833 --> 00:00:53,333
Whatever he told you, you had
to say yes, alright, you are right

17
00:00:53,833 --> 00:00:55,541
You were expected to listen

18
00:00:56,291 --> 00:00:58,666
Their words went in
one ear and out the other

19
00:00:58,916 --> 00:01:00,666
Because he would sit
there preaching to you

20
00:01:00,958 --> 00:01:04,583
Urging you and asking you
to pledge allegiance to them

21
00:01:05,041 --> 00:01:07,708
You would look at him and think to
yourself, This is a prophet sent from heaven
